OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe call-handler talked him through
OL,8,Fhow to perform CPR and at one point
OL,9,FStockton, who was off work ill, said
OL,10,Fhe would pass out if he tried to count
OL,11,Fthe compressions he was doing on the
OL,12,Ftoddler.
OL,14,FStockton was to tell paramedics,
OL,15,Fdoctors and the police that Charlie
OL,16,Fhad choked on a biscuit and that he
OL,17,Fpatted the child on the back and stuck
OL,18,Fhis fingers down the toddler's throat.
OL,20,FStockton said Charlie became "floppy"
OL,21,Fand so he called 999.
